AmTrust Financial Products, Services, and Insight





HomeVendorsAmTrust Financial
AmTrust FinancialVerified Vendorhttp://www.amtrustfi.com8663276904banksubmissions@amtrustgroup.comVendor800 Superior Avenue EOntario, OH44114Ownership: Privateamtrustnorthamerica/AmTrustNA-beta/2886324/

DescriptionAmTrust Financial Services, Inc. was founded in 1998 to provide property and casualty insurance to small businesses. In addition to being the nation's 4th largest insurer of Worker's Compensation, AmTrust is also a substantial writer of community banks. Their Financial Institutions team has over 20 years average industry experience insuring community banks and currently writes over 1,000 banks nationwide.ProductsSpecialty Coverage Insuranceon March 16, 2016

Excess Deposit Bond - A cost-effective means to provide depositors with coverage that is over and above the $250k provided by the FDIC


Civil Money Penalties Personal Protection - Covers the institution-affiliated party in the event Civil Money Penalties are assessed against that individual by a regulatory agency – an exposure no longer covered by a bank’s management liability policy


EFT Guard – Also known as “Corporate Account Takeover Coverage”  and protects a financial institution’s business banking customers for losses stemming from fraudulent ACH and wire transfers perpetrated through the customer’s system and outside of the financial institution


Professional Lines Insuranceon March 16, 2016

Directors & Officers – Provides A, B, and C coverage with additional $1M A-side specifically for bank Directors & Officers


Lender Liability - “Broad Form” coverage extends to suits brought by other persons or entities that may be damaged as a result of the lending or foreclosure process


Professional Services Liability- Covers claims due to errors or omissions involving professional services


Trust Liability - Covers claims due to errors or omissions involving trust services


Employment Practices Liability- Covers claims for actual or alleged wrongful acts such as discrimination, sexual harassment, and other employment-related causes of action


Fiduciary Liability - Covers claims for errors or omissions or negligent acts with respect to the administration of an employee benefit plan or breach of fiduciary duty or responsibilities imposed by ERISA, COBRA, HIPAA or similar laws


Cyber Liability - Protects the insured against losses for the failure to protect a customer’s information (SSN, credit card numbers, medical information, passwords, etc.) via theft, unauthorized access, viruses, or denial of service attack - includes Media Liability, Regulatory Defense, Crisis Mitigation, Cyber Extortion, and Business Interruption coverage


Financial Institution Bond - Provides the fidelity coverage required by regulators and covers various types of fraud exposures financial institutions inevitably face while doing business in the 21st century


Property & Casualty Insuranceon March 16, 2016

Property - Covers bank properties as well as building and tenant glass, attached and detached signage with no per-sign limitation, antennas and satellite dishes, vaults and ATMs, and electronic data processing


General Liability - Includes limits for bodily injury, property damage, personal and advertising injury


Commercial Auto - Ability to write on an owned auto or hired/non-owned only basis


Workers Compensation - Can coordinate with the General Liability for Employers Liability in monopolistic states


Umbrella - Available limits up to $10 million


Foreclosed Property – Ability to write foreclosures on a reporting form or individual basis


Force-Placed Property – Basic and special forms available


















